result.execSummary:
The defendant Nathaniel T Liedtke was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Theft-Movable Property <=$2500 [Modifiers: Repeater], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.20(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Defendant Nathaniel T Liedtke appears by videoconference from Milwaukee Secure Detention Facility, in custody.  Attorney Katie B. Bricco appears on behalf of Defendant.   Barbara Ann Michaels appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count #1.  Court perform plea colloquy and finds Defendant guilty of Count #1.  Count #2 is dismissed and read-in.  State gives sentencing recommendations.  Attorney Bricco makes statements regarding sentencing.  Defendant makes statements.  Court sentences the Defendant to the following:

COUNT #1:  IMPOSED SENTENCE OF:   

180 DAYS JAIL STRAIGHT TIME (CREDIT - 22 days)       CONSECUTIVE TO Case #15CM798

COSTS:  $253.00 & $200.00 DNA surcharge (to be paid as a condition of probation on Case #15CM798)

** Defendant to provide DNA sample, if not yet provided,   immediately if in custody otherwise within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department.**
